# Supabase Configuration
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# AI Search API (server-side only - NEVER expose to client)
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# 
# 1. GROQ_API_KEY must NEVER be prefixed with VITE_ 
#    (VITE_ prefix exposes variables to the client bundle)
#
# 2. Before deploying to production, update ALLOWED_ORIGINS in api/ai-search.ts
#    to match your actual domain(s)
#
# 3. The Supabase anon key is safe for client-side use because:
#    - Row Level Security (RLS) is enabled on all tables
#    - Users can only access their own data via auth.uid() checks
#
# 4. Rate limits are configured in api/ai-search.ts:
#    - 10 requests/minute per IP
#    - 3 requests/5s burst limit
#    - 500 requests/day global cap
#
# 5. For production, consider:
#    - Using Redis for rate limit persistence across serverless instances
#    - Adding Supabase JWT verification for authenticated-only access
#    - Setting up monitoring/alerting on API usage
